{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make DNA testing compulsory of every deceased person to solve unsolved crimes",
        "additional_details": "I bring this petition because too many families still suffer in silence after unsolved murders, rapes and disappearances. Parents can wait a lifetime to bury their child; children grow old without answers. Every year offenders die peacefully while victims\u2019 families are denied the truth. A simple DNA swab taken after death \u2014 potentially costing pennies \u2014 could finally give them closure. We feel this is basic British fairness: putting grieving victims first.",
        "background": "New law:\r\n\u2022 DNA mouth swab taken from every person who dies\r\n\u2022 Checked once against unsolved crimes\r\n\u2022 No match = destroyed immediately\r\n\u2022 Cost paid by the Government\r\n\u2022 Could solve thousands of cold cases\r\n\u2022 Put victims first",
